Mezzanine Fund
Plexus focuses on subordinated debt investments in middle market companies and has raised $950 million across four funds since 2005.  Currently investing out of Plexus Fund III  and Plexus Fund IV, $300 million and $400 million funds respectively, Plexus is a solution provider to middle market transactions.  We partner with:
 
• Existing Owners
• Management Teams
• Private Equity Funds
• Independent Sponsors
• Search Funds
 
We are long-term partners with the experience it takes to succeed.  Please contact us to see how we can help.
 
Criteria
 
Plexus invests in profitable businesses that need capital for growth, acquisitions, recapitalizations and buyouts.  Our focus is on operating companies with less than $100 million in revenue, a market our team has focused on our entire careers.
 
• All industries
• Subordinated debt and equity
• Growth, acquisitions, recapitalizations and buyouts
• Up to $20 million in EBITDA
 
We look for profitable businesses with a proven history of success.  We do not invest in real estate, early-stage companies or turnarounds.
 


